column159: At 11 I was diagnosed as ever so slightly on the autism spectrum, but I usually feel normal, at least nowadays.

Well there is a family history with my Brother and Nephew both receiving an ADHD diagnosis. We are all very similar, my father is too but he never was diagnosed but shares a lot of similarities as I do to those on the ADHD/Autism spectrum. I was a high achiever and well behaved at school so nothing was ever flagged despite my shocking social skills where I had to teach myself how to actually talk to people. I read internet guides because I knew I had to make friends otherwise I was down for a very hard time at secondary school. There is something there, but I am not sure what good it would do to know. Sure it would explain a lot, would be nice to know, but not essential. Neurodivergents have a strange affinity with me. A lot of my friends are on it and I can spot someone who is very easily. It's odd. They often remark I'm one of them but I laugh it off because who really knows? Not worth thinking about too much.
